cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with triangulations of a set of points in the plane and their properties, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of lower bounds and upper bounds for counting various types of graphs suggests that the paper may also belong to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of crossing-free straight-edge graphs and their embeddings suggests that the paper may also belong to graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
